#: C/network-applications.xml:2643(para) 
msgid "The following discussion assumes that you wish to enable TCP/IP connections and use the MD5 method for client authentication. PostgreSQL configuration files are stored in the <filename>/etc/postgresql/&lt;version&gt;/main</filename> directory. For example, if you install PostgreSQL 7.4, the configuration files are stored in the <filename>/etc/postgresql/7.4/main</filename> directory."
msgstr ""

